# 3. Fractional Knapsack

* Used to maximize profit in knapsack problems.
* Items can be divided into fractions.
* Greedy choice based on profit/weight ratio.
* Selects highest ratio items first.
* Efficient optimization technique.

Fractional Knapsack is a greedy algorithm where items are added to the knapsack according to their value-to-weight ratio.
Unlike the 0/1 Knapsack problem, items can be taken partially. The algorithm always chooses the item with the highest
profit per unit weight to maximize total profit.

### Example

```id="61m1ls"
Item  Profit Weight Ratio
A      60      10     6
B     100      20     5
C     120      30     4
```

