# 5. Job Sequencing Problem

* Schedules jobs to maximize profit.
* Each job has deadline and profit.
* Only one job can execute at a time.
* Greedy approach selects highest profit jobs.
* Deadlines must be satisfied.

The Job Sequencing Problem is solved using a greedy method to maximize total profit. Jobs are arranged in 
decreasing order of profit, and each job is scheduled before its deadline if a free slot is available.
This ensures maximum earnings within limited time slots.

### Example

```id="4h1bvm"
Job   Deadline Profit
J1       2       100
J2       1        50
J3       2        10
```

